Wash and dry all produce. Preheat oven to 425 degrees. Drain and rinse half the
@chickpeas{1%box} (save the rest for another use). Trim @zucchini{1}(trimmed) ends,
then dice into ½-inch cubes. Halve @heirloom grape tomatoes{4%oz}. Strip
@thyme{¼%oz} leaves from stems. Discard stems. Thinly slice @scallions{2}, keeping
greens and whites separate. Mince @garlic{2%cloves}. Halve @lemon{1}.

== Roasted Herbed Veggies ==

Toss zucchini, tomatoes, and half the thyme on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of
@olive oil{}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Roast about ~{10%minutes}, toss,
then continue roasting until golden brown, about another ~{10%minutes}.

== Crispy Chickpeas ==

Toss chickpeas in a #baking dish{} with @smoked paprika{1%tsp}, a drizzle of
@olive oil{}, and a pinch of salt and pepper. Roast about ~{10%minutes}, toss,
then continue roasting until crispy, about another ~{10%minutes}.

== Israeli Couscous ==

Heat @butter{1%tbsp}, garlic, and scallion whites in a #medium pot{} over medium-high
heat. Add @Israeli couscous{¾%cup} and remaining thyme, and stir to coat in butter.
Season with salt and pepper. Toss until slightly toasted, ~{2-3%minutes}. Add
@veggie stock concentrate{1} and 1 1/2 cups water. Bring to a boil, then reduce
to a simmer. Stir occasionally until al dente, ~{10-12%minutes}.

== Assembly ==

Add half the roasted veggies, half the @feta cheese{½%cup}, and a squeeze of lemon
to cooked couscous. Season with salt and pepper.

Plate couscous mixture, and top with remaining roasted veggies and crispy chickpeas.
Sprinkle with scallion greens and remaining feta. Enjoy!

> While we love chickpeas in any form, we have to admit: when roasted, they're
  pretty spectacular. We only use half the chickpeas, but leftovers make an
  amazing snack!